<@U055GGAHS|ian.shaun.thomas> uploaded a file: <https://androidchat.slack.com/files/ian.shaun.thomas/F0GFS2475/friday_gifdump_622_19.gif|Developer Expectations of Clients>

Because usually, when you just copy-paste an interface from an other platform to Android (or any other platform), you have many inconsistencies to the platforms designs. For example having buttons places on the lower part of the screen is fine in iOS but it’s not in Android because of the nav bar

Not saying that you can never ever have the same interface and behaviours “copy-pasted” across platforms, but you need to do some changed (sometimes small other times big) in order to be consistent with the platform
